3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If the printer is still operational: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do a Printhead quality check. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-45769776-F339-4201-8504-D964BD825ED6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2BA40A55-045A-41BA-8A55-30654DED507E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2BA40A55-045A-41BA-8A55-30654DED507E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Cool down the printheads. Use 
<xref keyref="SDS04-6-015" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-62E0BD73-612D-486D-8BA5-A6CC3815A3E3.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04-6-015 Cool down printheads [Special Tests]?>04-6-015 Cool down printheads [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Wait until the printheads are cooled down (40<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> C / 104<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup>F). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="00GENENGSERVWORKFLOW001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F7936095-9442-4058-9F8E-004B317DD3F1.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Service workflow on the system?>Service workflow on the system</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Place the top cover in the service position. See : 
<xref keyref="24DISA060" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-120956FD-BCBD-4084-9823-BCEEFB44C508.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to place the top cover in the service position?>24 How to place the top cover in the service position</xref> 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Prepare the components and tools. 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cut the bag near the seal (at the top). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Unpack the new printhead. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the printhead from the blister. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the red caps of the ink and air tube. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-99D7120E-F046-4DB3-BFEE-0A1A261D9893" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2EC298E5-CAF5-41C0-9CDE-383E7B91F133-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2EC298E5-CAF5-41C0-9CDE-383E7B91F133-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_9C8FE7906B3C491AA245876E73924120" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-899B14BE-1AF5-4C2F-86D1-FA5652A6F97F-low.png" id="IMAGE_C81F53E987404F328BBE6A8D83329800" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-899B14BE-1AF5-4C2F-86D1-FA5652A6F97F-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-24B084F3-4EB5-4959-A39A-462763612D10" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-72425E6C-3C14-47CE-BB3E-9E111E9A9757-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-72425E6C-3C14-47CE-BB3E-9E111E9A9757-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-102FA83E-8B69-46C4-94AB-C1F7E33B9E66" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-46FF26D1-CE7B-4799-B4B4-EDF4A2CE3F32-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-46FF26D1-CE7B-4799-B4B4-EDF4A2CE3F32-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-ECEDEBD8-6D40-49D8-874E-708F1E8B0062.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
